title: Shell injection on $HOME/~ credential paths via executable DataSource
updated_at: "2026-07-15T06:04:50Z"
---
## Problem
`catCommand` leaves any path starting with `$HOME` / `${HOME}` (and `~/…` after rewrite) unquoted so the shell expands `$HOME`. User-controlled `credentialsPath` or `customProfilesJson` values like `$HOME/foo; evil-command` or `~/x; evil` are executed by the executable DataSource. Absolute paths are correctly `shellQuote`d; home-relative ones are not.

## Location
contents/ui/ProfileController.qml:350-357

## Suggested fix
Always `shellQuote` the path segment after expanding `~`/`$HOME` in QML (e.g. resolve to an absolute path via a tiny helper script, or `cat "$HOME"/rest/with